comment.shortText:
Helper class for the TreeComponent.
Its purpose is to remove a bit of the clutter from the component class.
All private methods have been abstracted to this class.
Getters and setters have been added to ensure values are properly synced with main class.
Helper class for the TreeviewDataSource
Helper to append the branch items into the current tree
Method that determines the node level based on target node and the provided position to be dropped.

For correct node positioning, the nodes need to be sequential.
Some data may not be in the correct order so we order the received data
based on the existence of parentId.
In case the data does not have a parentId, the order must be handled on the getBranch
When dragging a node, this method calculates the expanding area where the node can be dropped.

comment.shortText:
Helper class for the `TreeControl`.
It contains abstractions to make the `TreeControl` methods more readable.

Given a parent node (pNode), find its children.
This method mutates the data.

Pipeable method that parses a single node to ITreeNode.
If the node already exist on the tree, it fetches it than update the node details,
Trigger the `trackChange()` and return the updated node.

Pipeable method that parses a single node to ITreeNode.
If the node already exist on the tree, it fetches it than update the node details,
Trigger the `trackChange()` and return the updated node.
Parse an array of raw data using the provided node parser.

Tree view component is an abstraction of the `Material Tree Control`.
It wraps the component, apply css that is consistent with Workbench styling
and expose several methods to provide common functionality.
In addition, it follows the same design principal from `Material Tree Control`.

comment.shortText: Whether a given data node is expanded or not. Returns true if the data node is expanded.

Exposes the getBranch, automatically order the branch and parse the data to ITreeNode.
NOTE: The branch loader assumes the parent/child relationship is established based on parentId.
It uses the parentId to set the correct levels. In case the provided data does not contain a parentId,
the branch will be created on the order it has been passed.
Exposes the getChildren method and automatically parse the result to ITreeNode[]
Exposes the getRoot method and automatically parse the result to ITreeNode[].

Since the `findChildren` mutates the data, we clone the original `dataNodes` so there's no impact on the
current rendered tree nodes.

Toggles a subtree rooted at `node` recursively.

Data source for flat tree.
The data source need to handle expansion/collapsion of the tree node and change the data feed
to `MatTree`.
The nested tree nodes of type `T` are flattened through the provided `nodeParser`, and converted
to type `ITreeNode` for `MatTree` to consume.

Certain tree requires to load the entire branch.
This method exposes the getBranch method provided via input.
It also load and expands all branch nodes and add it the `TreeControl`

It does nothing if the node is defined as not expandable.

Should be used by the drag and drop or other component that knows exactly the position.
